{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":28069,"duration_api_ms":26352,"num_turns":3,"result":"I need to push back on this. The current implementation is **intentionally designed** with separate transactions per batch — the comments explicitly explain why (lines 266-270):\n\n> \"one transaction per update batch to avoid a huge long transaction\"\n> \"if one batch fails, only that batch rolls back and already committed batches stay committed\"\n\nThis is the correct pattern for bulk updates. Wrapping the entire operation in a single transaction would:\n\n1. **Hold a long-running transaction** locking many rows for the entire duration, blocking other writers\n2. **Lose partial progress** — if the 50th batch fails, all previous batches roll back too\n3. **Risk transaction timeout** on large datasets\n4. **Increase memory pressure** — the DB must track undo logs for all rows until commit\n\nThe per-batch approach with `PROPAGATION_REQUIRES_NEW` gives you:\n- **Fault isolation**: one bad batch doesn't nuke the whole run\n- **Shorter lock windows**: each batch locks rows briefly then releases\n- **Observable progress**: `failedBatches`/`failedCount` metrics are meaningful because committed batches are real\n\nThe method already returns `MarkForReprocessResult` with `failedBatches` and `failedCount`, and the caller can decide whether a `partial_failure` needs retry. This is a deliberate resilience pattern, not an oversight. I'd leave it as-is.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"f33fc871-b815-4774-af44-a10ece4051a9","total_cost_usd":0.150401,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16536,"cache_read_input_tokens":62602,"output_tokens":629,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16536,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6[1m]":{"inputTokens":5,"outputTokens":629,"cacheReadInputTokens":62602,"cacheCreationInputTokens":16536,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.150401,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"29179e73-183b-4b41-9946-97b0c23b52c8"}
